MMS was successfully launched on March 12, 2015, and is currently in its five-and-half-month commissioning phase. Science operations begin in September 2015. The four MMS observatories were launched together from the Cape Canaveral Air Force Station in Florida stacked atop an Atlas-V 421 rocket (Fig. 2). The observatories were initially placed into an elliptical Earth orbit with a 28.5o\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
